question:
What will be the output of the following code snippet?

```java
try {
    int[] numbers = new int[5];
    numbers[10] = 50; // This line throws an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException
    System.out.print("A");
} catch (ArithmeticException e) {
    System.out.print("B");
} catch (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
    System.out.print("C");
} finally {
    System.out.print("D");
}
```

Consider the following code. What is the result of calling the method `problematicMethod()`?

```java
public void problematicMethod() {
    try {
        System.out.print("A");
        throw new RuntimeException("Oops!");
    } catch (RuntimeException e) {
        System.out.print("B");
        throw new IllegalStateException("New problem", e);
    } finally {
        System.out.print("C");
    }
}
```
